cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.DS

The paper deals with assessing the security of Industrial Control Systems (ICS) against cyber-physical threats, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and system and control theory (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a metric based on AND/OR hypergraphs, which involves optimization techniques such as MAX-SAT, indicating a possible connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents a Java-based security metric analyser for ICS, which suggests a potential link to software engineering (cs.SE).
